    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://jaeho-lee.github.io/research/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>jaeho.lee@postech.ac.kr (Jaeho Lee)</author>
      <guid>https://jaeho-lee.github.io/research/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;research&#34;&gt;research&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; href=&#34;#research&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;for an extended overview, see the &lt;a href=&#34;https://effl.postech.ac.kr&#34;&gt;group webpage&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My long-term goal is to make AI more &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;responsible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; &amp;mdash; accessible, sustainable, and righteous.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;To this end, I currently focus on &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI efficiency&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In particular, I aim to understand the fundamental trade-offs among three key factors:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;predictive performance&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;inference cost&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;training cost&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I believe that such an understanding can be gained by studying the &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;algorithmic biases&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; inherent in machine learning algorithms.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
